     4	obstruction rather than on a nearby reformulation.
     5	
     6	## Entries
     7	
     8	- `demand-estimate-level-action-on-the-live-obstruction.md`: make each
     9	  candidate identify the exact estimate, gain currency, quantity it shrinks,
    10	  and the ledger entry that proves the shrinkage after cutoff insertion.
    11	- `ask-which-identities-remain-exact-after-localization.md`: before comparing
    12	  rewrites, ask which identities survive the fixed cutoff and where the
    13	  resulting operator and commutator debt re-enters the estimate.
    14	- `for-geometry-branches-only-dynamic-coherence-or-persistence-clears-the-tao-screen.md`: static geometry usually collapses; only dynamic coherence, persistence, or a true stretching-facing algebraic lever should survive.
    15	- `name-the-first-hidden-stronger-assumption-in-comparator-audits.md`: make the
    16	  first smuggled upgrade explicit, since that is often where a comparator
    17	  really fails.
    18	- `use-a-bounded-shortlist-to-make-likely-collapse-an-earned-later-claim.md`:
    19	  even when the branch baseline looks negative, freeze a narrow candidate
    20	  table so later failure is audited rather than assumed.
    21	- `when-all-audited-candidates-are-only-dynamically-weak-stop-before-representation-work.md`:
    22	  when every audited route is only dynamically weak or static-only, stop the
    23	  chain before downstream representation work and demand a new ingredient.
    24	- `when-one-bad-term-and-one-gain-currency-are-frozen-a-tao-screen-may-end-the-branch.md`:
    25	  once one live term and one gain currency are fixed, a Tao screen may end the
    26	  branch with a bounded obstruction memo rather than a forced survivor list.

