+# Curator Details: Step 006 Exploration 002
+
+Date: `2026-03-31`
+Session: `codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-step-006-curator-002`
+
+## Inputs Processed
+
+- factual report:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/library-inbox/step-006-exploration-002-tao-screen-vorticity-biot-savart.md`
+- meta note:
+  `missions/beyond-de-giorgi/meta-inbox/meta-step-006-exploration-002.md`
+
+## Filing Decisions
+
+- Did not add a new standalone factual verdict file because the same
+  vorticity/Biot-Savart Step-2 rejection had already been filed later under
+  the unified Step-006 verdict in
+  `library/factual/exact-rewrite-obstruction-audit/vorticity-biot-savart-form-is-tao-insufficient-on-the-fixed-lei-ledger.md`.
+- Updated that existing factual atom with the exploration-002-specific
+  sharpening:
+  the only honest localized insertion point is formal substitution inside
+  `I_flux[phi]`, and any apparent rescue by stretching or geometry is branch
+  drift rather than survival of the rewrite candidate.
+- Updated
+  `library/factual/exact-rewrite-obstruction-audit/projected-and-vorticity-rewrites-must-pay-localization-debt.md`
+  because exploration 002 adds a cleaner candidate-level statement of where
+  the vorticity rewrite's debt re-enters the estimate.
+- Consolidated the meta point "variable choice is not yet a discriminator"
+  into
+  `library/meta/obstruction-screening/demand-estimate-level-action-on-the-live-obstruction.md`
+  instead of creating a near-duplicate meta file.
+- Added one new obstruction-screening note for the distinct lesson that if a
+  candidate only survives by drifting into stretching or geometry work, that
+  counts as failure of the original candidate rather than as a near miss.
+
+## Duplicate Check
+
+- Searched the factual and meta libraries for overlap on `vorticity`,
+  `Biot-Savart`, `Tao`, `frozen bad term`, `variable choice`, and
+  `architecture drift`.
+- Found existing general coverage for:
+  - the fixed bad term and same-protocol success criterion
+  - projected and vorticity rewrites owing localization debt
+  - the completed vorticity/Biot-Savart Step-2 rejection from the unified
+    Step-006 curation
+- Found no existing meta entry that already states the branch-drift lesson in
+  reusable obstruction-screening form.
+
+## Index Updates
+
+- Updated `library/factual/exact-rewrite-obstruction-audit/INDEX.md` so the
+  vorticity entry now mentions branch drift explicitly.
+- Updated `library/factual/INDEX.md` so the topic summary now includes
+  branch-drift failure modes inside the fixed exact-rewrite audit.
+- Updated `library/meta/obstruction-screening/INDEX.md` and
+  `library/meta/INDEX.md` so the new architecture-drift rule is discoverable
+  from both topic levels.
+
+## Conflict Resolution
+
+- The main factual verdict had already been curated from a later unified
+  report. I resolved that by updating the existing factual note with the
+  earlier report's missing insertion-point and branch-drift detail instead of
+  creating a duplicate file.
+- The meta note mixed one lesson already covered by the live-obstruction entry
+  with one genuinely new lesson about architecture drift. I merged the first
+  into the existing file and filed the second as one compact new meta note.
+
+## Deletion Policy
+
+- The inbox report and meta note were left in place as requested.

